<document xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0"
          xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
          xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/XDOC/2.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/xdoc-2.0.xsd">

    <properties>
        <title>Download Instructions</title>
        <author>Toby Weston</author>
    </properties>

    <body>
        <section name="Download Instructions">
            <p>
                The project is published via the <a href="https://maven-repository.dev.java.net/">java.net</a>
                Maven repository.
            </p>
            <p>
                You can download the source and binary jar directly from
                <a href="http://download.java.net/maven/2/com/google/code/tempus-fugit/">
                http://download.java.net/maven/2/com/google/code/tempus-fugit/</a> or use Maven or Ivy.
            </p>
            <p>
               <font color="red"><b>Note</b> that if the current version is a SNAPSHOT version (see top right), the Maven repository version
               may not contain the bleeding edge jar and so may not include all the classes described in this document. </font>
            </p>

            <subsection name="Maven 2">
            <p>
                Add the java.net repository to your project's <code>pom.xml</code>, or into Maven's configuration
                (using <code>conf/settings.xml</code>).
            </p>
<source>
&lt;repository&gt;
  &lt;id&gt;java.net&lt;/id&gt;
  &lt;url&gt;http://download.java.net/maven/1&lt;/url&gt;
  &lt;layout&gt;legacy&lt;/layout&gt;
&lt;/repository&gt;
</source>
            </subsection>
            <p>
                Then add a <code>dependency</code> as usualy to your <code>pom.xml</code>.
            </p>
            <source>
&lt;dependency&gt;
  &lt;groupId&gt;com.google.code.tempus-fugit&lt;/groupId&gt;
  &lt;artifactId&gt;tempus-fugit&lt;/artifactId&gt;
  &lt;version&gt;${project.version}&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt; </source>
            <subsection name="Ivy">
            <p>
                For Ivy, add the following definition to your <code>ivysettings.xml</code> to download from the repository.
            </p>
            <source>
&lt;ibiblio name="java.net" root="http://download.java.net/maven/1/" namespace="java.net" pattern="[organization]/jars/[module]-[revision].[ext]" /&gt;
</source>
            <p>
                You can then add the following to your project's <code>ivy.xml</code>.
            </p>
            <source>&lt;dependency org="com.google.code.tempus-fugit" name="tempus-fugit" rev="1.0-SNAPSHOT" conf="netstream-runtime"/&gt; </source>
            </subsection>

            <subsection name="Source Code and Issue Tracking">
                <p>
                    Feel free to browse the source code and send comments and feedback. Any issues (bugs) you might
                    discover can be raised and tracked through the issue management system.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><p><a href="source-repository.html">Source</a></p></li>
                    <li><p><a href="issue-tracking.html">Issue Tracking</a></p></li>
                </ul>
            </subsection>
        </section>

    </body>
